tches (`stats1.errors_z`, `stats1.errortime_z`).\\n*   **Display on First Mismatch:** The requirement mandates displaying input signals (`clk`, `reset`, `w`) and output signals (`z_dut`, `z_ref`) at the time of the *first* mismatch. I will implement a task `display_signals` and trigger it when `stats1.errors == 0` and a mismatch occurs.\\n*   **Final Reporting:** The final reporting must be: \\n    *   If no mismatch: `SIMULATION PASSED`.\\n    *   If mismatch: `SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y` (where \'x\' refers to the general mismatch count, as per the requirement interpretation of \'x MISMATCHES\').\\n*   **Signal Display Format:** For multi-bit signals (though all used signals are 1-bit here, the logic must support it), I need to display HEX and BIN.\\n*   **Syntax Correction:** I corrected the typo `sstats1.errors_z` to `stats1.errors_z` in the previous TB\'s `always` block. I also streamlined the final reporting to match the exact required format, replacing the old `final` block with a structured timeout/final check block.\\n*   **Data Types:** The structure definition `typeof struct packed` is used, which is cleaner than `typedef struct packed` in some contexts, but I will stick to `typedef` as used in the golden TB structure, while fixing the capitalization/syntax issues observed in the log.\\n\\n**Advice to avoid syntax errors:**\\n1.  **Module Declaration:** Ensure every module starts with `module ModuleName (...)` and ends with `endmodule`.\\n2.  **Port Matching:** When instantiating modules, ensure the port names and types exactly match the interface definition.\\n3.  **Task/Function Scope:** Tasks and functions must be defined within the scope where they are used, and their arguments/local variables must be correctly declared.\\n4.  **Assignment vs. Blocking:** In sequential blocks (`always @(posedge clk)`), always use non-blocking assignments (`<=`). In combinational blocks (`always @(*)`) or procedural assignments, use blocking assignments (`=`).\\n5.  **Variable Naming:** Be careful with typos, especially when referencing structure members (e.g., `stats1.errors` vs `sstats1.errors`).\\n\\nI will ensure the final reporting logic correctly uses `stats1.errors` for the count \'x\' and `stats1.errortime` for the time \'y\', as per the strict requirement.",\n    "interface": "module TopModule (\\n    input  logic clk,\\n    input  logic reset,\\n    input  logic w,\\n    output logic z\\n);\\nendmodule",\n    "testbench": "`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\\n`define OK 12\\n`define INCORRECT 13\\n\\n// Assuming RefModule exists and matches the necessary interface for compilation\\nmodule RefModule (\\n    input clk,\\n    input reset,\\n    input w,\\n    output z\\n);\\n    // Dummy implementation for compilation completeness\\n    assign z = 1\'b0;\\nendmodule\\n\\nmodule stimulus_gen (\\n\\tinput clk,\\n\\toutput logic reset,\\n\\toutput logic w\\n);\\n\\tinitial begin\\n\\t\\trepeat(200) @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\tw <= $random;\\n\\t\\treset <= ($random & 15) == 0;\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t#1 $finish;\\n\\tend\\nendmodule\\n\\nmodule tb();\\n\\t\\n\\ttypedef struct packed {\\n\\t\\tint errors;\\n\\t\\tint errortime;\\n\\t\\tint errors_z;\\n\\t\\tint errortime_z;\\n\\t\\tint clocks;\\n\\t} stats;\\n\\t\\n\\tstats stats1;\\n\\t\\n\\t// Variables kept from original testbench structure for compatibility\\n\\twire[511:0] wavedrom_title;\\n\\twire wavedrom_enable;\\n\\tint wavedrom_hide_after_time;\\n\\t\\n\\treg clk=0;\\n\\tinitial forever\\n\\t\\t#5 clk = ~clk;\\n\\n\\tlogic reset;\\n\\tlogic w;\\n\\tlogic z_ref;\\n\\tlogic z_dut;\\n\\n\\tinitial begin \\n\\t\\t$dumpfile(\\"wave.vcd\\");\\n\\t\\t$dumpvars(1, stim1.clk, tb_mismatch ,clk,reset,w,z_ref,z_dut );\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\n\\twire tb_match;\\n\\twire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\\n\\t\\n\\tstimulus_gen stim1 (\\n\\t\\t.clk, \\n\\t\\t.* , // Following golden testbench structure\\n\\t\\t.reset,\\n\\t\\tw );\\n\\tRefModule good1 (\\n\